1
00:00:02,200 --> 00:00:08,190
♪

2
00:00:08,190 --> 00:00:11,280
(singing in foreign language)

3
00:00:11,280 --> 00:01:44,160
♪

4
00:01:48,120 --> 00:01:51,160
In our last episode, after
sharing a moment with Yumi,

5
00:01:51,160 --> 00:01:53,230
Shishio begins his
battle with Kenshin,

6
00:01:53,230 --> 00:01:56,090
who finds himself
fighting for his life.

7
00:01:56,090 --> 00:02:12,170
♪

8
00:02:12,170 --> 00:02:15,190
(yelling)

9
00:02:15,190 --> 00:02:25,050
♪

10
00:02:31,050 --> 00:02:34,020
(fire roaring)

11
00:02:41,140 --> 00:02:43,230
(whimpering)

12
00:02:43,230 --> 00:03:07,160
♪

13
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:10,280
Survival of the fittest,
it's the only way.

14
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:12,230
So I've heard.

15
00:03:12,230 --> 00:03:15,030
The strong will live,
the weak will die.

16
00:03:15,030 --> 00:03:17,290
To Sojiro, this meant merely
being the strongest fighter,

17
00:03:17,290 --> 00:03:21,130
but in fact, it means a
great deal more that that.

18
00:03:21,130 --> 00:03:22,270
It's fundamental.

19
00:03:22,270 --> 00:03:24,200
It's a law of nature.

20
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:26,260
♪

21
00:03:26,260 --> 00:03:31,120
The weak exist only as
fodder for the strong.

22
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:33,120
But throughout history,
there have been times

23
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:36,180
when great multitudes of
weak men have banded together,

24
00:03:36,180 --> 00:03:39,050
and with the strength of their
numbers, they've subverted

25
00:03:39,050 --> 00:03:41,040
and suppressed
the laws of nature,

26
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:42,160
and now it's happening again!

27
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:46,020
The Meiji government
is an obscenity!

28
00:03:46,020 --> 00:03:50,090
But soon I will take control
and lead Japan to glory.

29
00:03:50,090 --> 00:03:51,220
You are a killer
who lived through

30
00:03:51,220 --> 00:03:53,270
the bloody end of
the Tokugawa era.

31
00:03:53,270 --> 00:03:55,190
You understand
that we must abide

32
00:03:55,190 --> 00:03:57,250
by the fundamental
law of nature.

33
00:03:57,250 --> 00:04:01,220
The strong will live, the weak
can be used, then discarded.

34
00:04:01,220 --> 00:04:04,060
The strong cannot be
subservient to the weak.

35
00:04:04,060 --> 00:04:06,090
You agree, don't you?

36
00:04:06,090 --> 00:04:07,230
No, I don't.

37
00:04:07,230 --> 00:04:11,000
♪

38
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,130
No human being in a free society

39
00:04:13,130 --> 00:04:16,080
should be regarded as less
valuable than any other.

40
00:04:16,080 --> 00:04:18,100
The people of this country
that you call fodder

41
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:20,240
are the ones that give it
stability and its strength.

42
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:23,050
All they ever asked
for was peace,

43
00:04:23,050 --> 00:04:25,130
and now after living
through the bloodiest era

44
00:04:25,130 --> 00:04:27,290
Japan has ever seen,
they've got it,

45
00:04:27,290 --> 00:04:29,120
now you wanna destroy them,

46
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:31,110
and I'll do whatever
I can to stop you.

47
00:04:31,110 --> 00:04:33,030
But you cannot stop me.

48
00:04:33,030 --> 00:04:35,070
I must fulfill my destiny.

49
00:04:35,070 --> 00:04:38,140
Your destiny is to lose.

50
00:04:38,140 --> 00:04:41,250
♪

51
00:04:41,250 --> 00:04:44,010
No matter how brilliant
Shishio's arguments are,

52
00:04:44,010 --> 00:04:45,220
Kenshin's beliefs
are too strong.

53
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:47,080
He won't budge an inch,

54
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:48,270
but Shishio already knows that.

55
00:04:48,270 --> 00:04:50,240
The reason he wants
Kenshin to keep talking

56
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:53,010
is because Kenshin's
already weak from his wounds,

57
00:04:53,010 --> 00:04:55,160
and the longer they talk
the weaker he'll get.

58
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:57,260
♪

59
00:04:57,260 --> 00:05:00,090
You're lying to yourself,
Kenshin Himura.

60
00:05:00,090 --> 00:05:03,160
I know that deep within
your heart you agree with me.

61
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:05,070
I know all about you, Kenshin.

62
00:05:05,070 --> 00:05:08,200
Your reputation as a merciless
slasher was well-deserved.

63
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:10,290
I wonder what you
find more embarrassing.

64
00:05:10,290 --> 00:05:12,290
The fact that you killed
all those people,

65
00:05:12,290 --> 00:05:16,030
or your pathetic attempt to
try to deny who you really are.

66
00:05:16,030 --> 00:05:17,290
♪

67
00:05:17,290 --> 00:05:20,160
You're a warrior,
Kenshin, I know you are.

68
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:22,000
The question is,

69
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,190
are you a better
warrior than I am?

70
00:05:24,190 --> 00:05:27,160
Unfortunately for you,
the answer is no

71
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:32,030
which means that
you're going to die!

72
00:05:32,030 --> 00:05:33,280
Yeah, I'll die,

73
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:35,200
but I won't die today.

74
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:39,000
Not at the hands of
a maniac like you.

75
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,290
I want the fighting to be
over, I want to live in peace.

76
00:05:41,290 --> 00:05:44,240
(grunting)

77
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:47,040
Oh no, he's losing.

78
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,040
Hm.

79
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:49,240
(laughing)

80
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:52,130
So you think you're hot stuff?

81
00:05:52,130 --> 00:05:54,020
Stop kidding yourself.

82
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:56,180
The truth is that there are
countries all over the world

83
00:05:56,180 --> 00:05:58,110
who are at war with each other.

84
00:05:58,110 --> 00:06:00,160
The European countries
are setting up colonies

85
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:02,190
wherever they can.

86
00:06:02,190 --> 00:06:04,080
The British control India,

87
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:07,020
a country 12 times
the size of their own,

88
00:06:07,020 --> 00:06:08,290
and other powers are
establishing colonies

89
00:06:08,290 --> 00:06:11,180
in the China Sea which could
choke off our trade routes,

90
00:06:11,180 --> 00:06:14,190
and could be staging
areas to attack Japan.

91
00:06:14,190 --> 00:06:16,250
And what has our
government done about it?

92
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:18,160
Nothing, the only
thing they care about

93
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:20,150
is political maneuvering
and making certain

94
00:06:20,150 --> 00:06:22,220
that they remain in power.

95
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:24,290
The other military powers
of the world are well aware

96
00:06:24,290 --> 00:06:26,210
of our government's weakness,

97
00:06:26,210 --> 00:06:29,120
and if Japan continues
on its present course,

98
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:32,060
we'll end up as a
colony, not a country.

99
00:06:32,060 --> 00:06:34,060
Our so-called leaders
have to be replaced

100
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:36,110
in order to preserve
the honor of Japan.

101
00:06:36,110 --> 00:06:38,280
♪

102
00:06:38,280 --> 00:06:40,240
Kenshin's getting
weaker by the moment.

103
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:42,290
First he was wounded
in his duel with Aoshi,

104
00:06:42,290 --> 00:06:45,160
and before he had a chance
to recover he fought Sojiro

105
00:06:45,160 --> 00:06:48,180
who cut him up pretty badly
before Kenshin finally won.

106
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:51,040
If Kenshin waits any longer
he might not be strong enough

107
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:52,090
to beat Shishio.

108
00:06:52,090 --> 00:06:57,090
♪

109
00:06:57,090 --> 00:07:00,070
(groaning)

110
00:07:00,070 --> 00:07:10,130
♪

111
00:07:10,130 --> 00:07:12,200
Sojiro told me all
about your law of nature,

112
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:14,160
the survival of the fittest.

113
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:17,160
You warped and twisted that poor
kid into an inhuman heartless

114
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:20,210
monster without the ability
to feel anything for anyone.

115
00:07:20,210 --> 00:07:23,100
♪

116
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:26,260
The strong will live,
and the weak will die.

117
00:07:26,260 --> 00:07:30,130
It's the natural
order of things,

118
00:07:30,130 --> 00:07:32,150
yet you go on trying
to protect the weak.

119
00:07:32,150 --> 00:07:35,100
I can't understand
why you would do that.

120
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:37,270
Why waste time on people
who aren't relevant?

121
00:07:37,270 --> 00:07:41,000
Mr. Shishio taught me to
concern myself only with people

122
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,060
who were strong enough
to be dangerous,

123
00:07:43,060 --> 00:07:46,210
how to recognize who they were,
and how to eliminate them.

124
00:07:46,210 --> 00:07:48,140
Mr. Shishio gave me this sword.

125
00:07:48,140 --> 00:07:50,200
Without it I wouldn't
have survived.

126
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:52,260
I never wanted to kill anyone.

127
00:07:52,260 --> 00:07:56,080
It was Mr. Shishio who taught me
that I didn't have any choice.

128
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:58,290
If I hadn't killed them,
they would've killed me.

129
00:07:58,290 --> 00:08:01,250
But still, the truth is,

130
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:04,050
I never wanted to kill anyone.

131
00:08:04,050 --> 00:08:06,200
You used Sojiro
like everyone else.

132
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,220
You knew he couldn't win.

133
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:10,020
You had us fight in
order to weaken me.

134
00:08:10,020 --> 00:08:12,080
Yes, exactly.

135
00:08:12,080 --> 00:08:13,270
I'll do whatever
it takes to win.

136
00:08:13,270 --> 00:08:16,280
In this case, I used
Sojiro's fanatical loyalty.

137
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:18,240
I knew he would wound
you badly enough

138
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:21,190
to drain most of your strength.

139
00:08:21,190 --> 00:08:24,150
He even gave me the
ultimate farewell gift.

140
00:08:24,150 --> 00:08:26,170
He told me how
to protect myself

141
00:08:26,170 --> 00:08:30,140
against your secret
sword-strike technique.

142
00:08:30,140 --> 00:08:32,090
A farewell gift?

143
00:08:32,090 --> 00:08:35,200
I'm glad to hear it, there's
hope for Sojiro after all.

144
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,220
Huh?

145
00:08:36,220 --> 00:08:38,210
I wouldn't expect you
to understand, Shishio,

146
00:08:38,210 --> 00:08:40,010
so I'll explain it to you.

147
00:08:40,010 --> 00:08:42,080
For the first time in his life,
Sojiro has given something

148
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:44,030
to someone simply
because he wanted to,

149
00:08:44,030 --> 00:08:45,150
not for his own benefit.

150
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:48,030
He's not under your
control anymore, Shishio.

151
00:08:48,030 --> 00:08:49,180
He's realized that
there's more to life

152
00:08:49,180 --> 00:08:50,290
than being the strongest,

153
00:08:50,290 --> 00:08:54,010
and now he'll find
his own answers.

154
00:08:54,010 --> 00:08:57,180
I want an answer too,
Kenshin, remember?

155
00:08:57,180 --> 00:08:59,210
I asked if you were
strong enough to beat me,

156
00:08:59,210 --> 00:09:02,070
and that question can only
be answered with action.

157
00:09:02,070 --> 00:09:04,250
You can't hide behind
your words any longer.

158
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:07,100
All right, Shishio,
make your move.

159
00:09:07,100 --> 00:09:09,030
Yes, I think it's finally time

160
00:09:09,030 --> 00:09:11,160
to say goodbye
to Kenshin Himura.

161
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:14,180
(shouting)

162
00:09:14,180 --> 00:09:20,070
♪

163
00:09:20,070 --> 00:09:23,000
No, it's too soon
for you to die.

164
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:26,270
♪

165
00:09:26,270 --> 00:09:29,070
I know that smell.

166
00:09:29,070 --> 00:09:31,080
At least you'll die
having the satisfaction

167
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:32,280
of a glorious death.

168
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:33,270
Gunpowder.

169
00:09:33,270 --> 00:09:35,150
No!

170
00:09:35,150 --> 00:09:39,000
(laughing)

171
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:44,020
♪

172
00:09:44,020 --> 00:09:46,090
Kenshin!

173
00:09:46,090 --> 00:10:02,130
♪

174
00:10:02,130 --> 00:10:04,000
No, dead?

175
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,240
♪

176
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:09,040
Poor Kenshin, I
can't believe it.

177
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:16,190
♪

178
00:10:16,190 --> 00:10:18,140
What's this, dead already?

179
00:10:18,140 --> 00:10:21,040
And I was going to
make him suffer.

180
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:23,010
I'm disappointed, I thought
you'd provide a lot more

181
00:10:23,010 --> 00:10:24,220
entertainment than this.

182
00:10:24,220 --> 00:10:27,040
Ha, it's really a pity.

183
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:30,030
Nine minutes and
fifty-three seconds.

184
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:32,260
There was no need
to worry after all.

185
00:10:32,260 --> 00:10:35,000
I would never have believed
it if I hadn't seen it

186
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,080
with my own two eyes.

187
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:38,220
Gunpowder hidden in
the glove of his armor,

188
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:41,100
and he set it off just
as he struck Himura.

189
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:43,110
A brilliant strategy,
Mr. Shishio.

190
00:10:43,110 --> 00:10:45,080
Absolutely brilliant.

191
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:46,270
Enough of your
compliments, Hoji.

192
00:10:46,270 --> 00:10:48,180
See to it this
mess is cleaned up.

193
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:50,200
Yes, sir.

194
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:55,230
A wise warrior once said that
it's dangerous to let down

195
00:10:55,230 --> 00:11:00,100
your guard until all of your
enemies have been defeated.

196
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:03,070
(screaming)

197
00:11:10,050 --> 00:11:11,100
Saito!

198
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:14,070
(yelling)

199
00:11:18,250 --> 00:11:23,020
-Mr. Shishio!
-Ahh!

200
00:11:23,020 --> 00:11:24,240
He's got ya!

201
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:27,210
(shouting)

202
00:11:29,030 --> 00:11:30,170
Ha!

203
00:11:37,230 --> 00:11:39,110
Great.

204
00:11:39,110 --> 00:11:41,070
Saito hit him perfectly.

205
00:11:41,070 --> 00:11:42,270
How could Shishio
have even survived

206
00:11:42,270 --> 00:11:44,160
a killer blow like that?

207
00:11:44,160 --> 00:11:57,080
♪

208
00:11:57,080 --> 00:11:59,170
I knew you would
come eventually.

209
00:11:59,170 --> 00:12:03,270
♪

210
00:12:03,270 --> 00:12:06,060
I know how clever
you are, Saito,

211
00:12:06,060 --> 00:12:09,270
and that somehow you've managed
to learn many of my secrets,

212
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:13,230
but you didn't know
about this one, did you?

213
00:12:13,230 --> 00:12:16,140
A steel crown.

214
00:12:16,140 --> 00:12:18,070
Ten years ago, when
agents of the government

215
00:12:18,070 --> 00:12:20,290
tried to assassinate me,
they knocked me unconscious

216
00:12:20,290 --> 00:12:22,120
with a blow to the head.

217
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:26,060
It caused permanent
damage to my skull.

218
00:12:26,060 --> 00:12:29,240
So I have made certain that
it will never happen again.

219
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:31,190
I'm afraid you didn't
do you research

220
00:12:31,190 --> 00:12:34,110
quite well enough, Saito Hajime.

221
00:12:34,110 --> 00:12:37,150
You lost the only chance
you had to destroy me.

222
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:40,090
♪

223
00:12:40,090 --> 00:12:42,070
You must have received
that wound on your leg

224
00:12:42,070 --> 00:12:43,260
when you fought Usui.

225
00:12:43,260 --> 00:12:47,140
At least he did something
right before he died.

226
00:12:47,140 --> 00:12:50,120
Actually, considering the
severity of your wound,

227
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:53,200
I'm surprised you were able
to mount such a strong attack.

228
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:55,230
It really was quite impressive.

229
00:12:55,230 --> 00:12:57,090
Shame you have to die.

230
00:12:57,090 --> 00:13:00,260
(flames hissing)

231
00:13:00,260 --> 00:13:02,220
But look at the bright side.

232
00:13:02,220 --> 00:13:04,070
When you get to the other world,

233
00:13:04,070 --> 00:13:06,290
you and Battousai will
have a lot to talk about.

234
00:13:06,290 --> 00:13:10,080
Perhaps, but I haven't
finished with you yet, Shishio.

235
00:13:10,080 --> 00:13:14,160
I am going to kill
you or die trying.

236
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:17,220
Your dedication is admirable,
but what I don't understand

237
00:13:17,220 --> 00:13:20,140
is why a former member
of the Shinsen group

238
00:13:20,140 --> 00:13:22,280
would fight for the sake
of a corrupt government.

239
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:26,010
They don't deserve your
loyalty, and you know it.

240
00:13:26,010 --> 00:13:28,110
I think you're fighting
for some other reason,

241
00:13:28,110 --> 00:13:31,190
some lame sense of righteousness
like your friend Kenshin.

242
00:13:31,190 --> 00:13:32,240
Is that it?

243
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:34,160
The reason I fight
is because I believe

244
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:37,070
in a very simple philosophy.

245
00:13:37,070 --> 00:13:39,180
Those who are evil
must be destroyed,

246
00:13:39,180 --> 00:13:41,200
killed immediately.

247
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:45,200
♪

248
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:46,280
Good.

249
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:50,140
Finally a man with a philosophy
that's easy to understand.

250
00:13:50,140 --> 00:13:53,140
Unfortunately, a man
who's also about to die.

251
00:13:53,140 --> 00:14:03,010
♪

252
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:04,240
That's enough talk.

253
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:14,020
♪

254
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:15,250
You're not as strong
as you used to be.

255
00:14:15,250 --> 00:14:18,120
I'm afraid your wounds
have taken their toll.

256
00:14:18,120 --> 00:14:21,260
♪

257
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:25,160
You see, your fight with Usui
was part of my master plan.

258
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:26,230
I assumed you would win

259
00:14:26,230 --> 00:14:28,160
and that you would
probably kill him,

260
00:14:28,160 --> 00:14:32,040
but I also knew that
he would dissipate you.

261
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:34,210
You must admit my
plan worked perfectly.

262
00:14:34,210 --> 00:14:37,160
Yet even if you'd been at full
strength you couldn't have won.

263
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:40,150
I've seen you fight often enough
to know all your techniques.

264
00:14:40,150 --> 00:14:41,270
Huh?

265
00:14:41,270 --> 00:14:51,110
♪

266
00:14:51,110 --> 00:14:53,120
Saito knows he doesn't
stand a chance,

267
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:54,290
but he won't give up.

268
00:14:54,290 --> 00:14:56,230
Now that Kenshin
has been taken out,

269
00:14:56,230 --> 00:14:59,050
he feels that he and his
Gatotsu are all that remains

270
00:14:59,050 --> 00:15:01,170
to keep Shishio from
completing his plan

271
00:15:01,170 --> 00:15:05,080
to destroy the government
and become dictator of Japan.

272
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:07,020
♪

273
00:15:07,020 --> 00:15:08,120
That's enough.

274
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:11,230
We are wasting time, come on.

275
00:15:11,230 --> 00:15:16,010
You know the end is inevitable,
so why put it off any longer?

276
00:15:16,010 --> 00:15:18,030
It's time to say goodbye.

277
00:15:18,030 --> 00:15:19,290
Attack while you can.

278
00:15:19,290 --> 00:15:22,160
Quickly.

279
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:24,050
Fang Thrust Two!

280
00:15:24,050 --> 00:15:37,070
♪

281
00:15:37,070 --> 00:15:39,080
Flying Fang Thrust!

282
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:45,090
♪

283
00:15:45,090 --> 00:15:49,140
(gasping)

284
00:15:49,140 --> 00:15:53,030
(grunting)

285
00:15:53,030 --> 00:15:55,190
♪

286
00:15:55,190 --> 00:15:57,010
Like I said, Saito.

287
00:15:57,010 --> 00:15:59,040
I know all your secrets,
all your tricks.

288
00:15:59,040 --> 00:16:02,070
Can't you see it's hopeless?

289
00:16:02,070 --> 00:16:07,070
All I see is an arrogant bastard
who I'm going to kill now!

290
00:16:07,070 --> 00:16:09,180
Fang Thrust Zero!

291
00:16:09,180 --> 00:16:22,130
♪

292
00:16:22,130 --> 00:16:24,040
(laughing)

293
00:16:24,040 --> 00:16:25,230
It's the end, my friend.

294
00:16:25,230 --> 00:16:28,110
♪

295
00:16:28,110 --> 00:16:30,050
You're not feeling so well.

296
00:16:30,050 --> 00:16:33,130
I must admit, you lasted
longer than I thought you would.

297
00:16:33,130 --> 00:16:36,280
For a government man, you fought
very well, and honorably.

298
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:40,140
I promise, when historians
write about my rise to power,

299
00:16:40,140 --> 00:16:43,070
I'll make certain they
mention how well you fought.

300
00:16:43,070 --> 00:16:46,080
Farewell, Saito Hajime.

301
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:47,230
You were a worthy opponent.

302
00:16:47,230 --> 00:16:50,230
(screaming)

303
00:16:50,230 --> 00:16:56,150
♪

304
00:17:05,290 --> 00:17:08,260
(laughing)

305
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:13,220
Ohh.

306
00:17:13,220 --> 00:17:16,200
♪

307
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:17,240
You?

308
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:23,020
♪

309
00:17:23,020 --> 00:17:24,220
You're still here?

310
00:17:24,220 --> 00:17:27,030
Lucky for you, I'm
feeling generous.

311
00:17:27,030 --> 00:17:29,130
I won't kill
cowards, you can go.

312
00:17:29,130 --> 00:17:31,240
I don't accept your generosity,

313
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:34,140
and I'm not going
anywhere, not quite yet.

314
00:17:34,140 --> 00:17:37,230
I don't mind dying as long
as I take you with me.

315
00:17:37,230 --> 00:17:39,280
(laughing)

316
00:17:39,280 --> 00:17:42,040
The only way you
could kill me, Sano,

317
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:44,160
is in your dreams,
that's the only way.

318
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:46,220
I can't believe that even
you would be foolish enough

319
00:17:46,220 --> 00:17:49,150
to want to fight me after
what you've seen here today.

320
00:17:49,150 --> 00:17:51,200
The secret sword technique
of Kenshin Himura,

321
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:54,220
the legendary Battousai
the Slasher wasn't enough.

322
00:17:54,220 --> 00:17:56,160
Neither was the
Gatotsu of Saito,

323
00:17:56,160 --> 00:18:00,030
the most formidable fighter
of the Shinsen group.

324
00:18:00,030 --> 00:18:03,210
Their perseverance and bravery
did them no good in the end.

325
00:18:03,210 --> 00:18:06,090
The strong live,
and the weak die.

326
00:18:06,090 --> 00:18:09,020
You mean survival
of the fittest?

327
00:18:09,020 --> 00:18:10,100
Exactly.

328
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:12,060
You're like a cannibal, Shishio.

329
00:18:12,060 --> 00:18:15,090
You devour other human
beings in order to survive.

330
00:18:15,090 --> 00:18:17,020
What's for lunch?

331
00:18:17,020 --> 00:18:19,280
No human can be like that!

332
00:18:19,280 --> 00:18:20,280
Kenshin was right.

333
00:18:20,280 --> 00:18:24,240
You're a freak of
nature, an abomination.

334
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:27,050
The Meiji Restoration
started 10 years ago,

335
00:18:27,050 --> 00:18:28,290
but there's still so much to do.

336
00:18:28,290 --> 00:18:31,140
Right now, the weak are
still being oppressed

337
00:18:31,140 --> 00:18:33,210
all over our country
by the strong,

338
00:18:33,210 --> 00:18:36,090
but I know that
the future of Japan

339
00:18:36,090 --> 00:18:39,020
depends on the beliefs and
principles of the Restoration

340
00:18:39,020 --> 00:18:41,190
being accepted by all the
peoples of our country.

341
00:18:41,190 --> 00:18:45,030
The old ways won't work anymore.

342
00:18:45,030 --> 00:18:47,120
That's why Shishio has to go.

343
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:49,040
Guys like him would rather die

344
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:51,270
than live in a world
of peace and justice.

345
00:18:51,270 --> 00:18:56,080
♪

346
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:58,100
You know, Kenshin used
his sword to protect people

347
00:18:58,100 --> 00:19:00,020
who couldn't protect themselves.

348
00:19:00,020 --> 00:19:01,110
He was trying to
build something,

349
00:19:01,110 --> 00:19:04,080
not destroy everything
like you're trying to do.

350
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:07,150
And the result is he's dead.

351
00:19:07,150 --> 00:19:10,100
Go away, Sanosuke Sagara.

352
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:12,290
There's nothing more
you can do here.

353
00:19:12,290 --> 00:19:15,020
I'm not through with you yet!

354
00:19:15,020 --> 00:19:17,250
(yelling)

355
00:19:17,250 --> 00:19:25,150
♪

356
00:19:25,150 --> 00:19:27,240
Let's not waste time.

357
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:30,030
(groaning)

358
00:19:30,030 --> 00:19:32,190
♪

359
00:19:32,190 --> 00:19:36,060
Hoji, you can kill him
now or just let him die.

360
00:19:36,060 --> 00:19:38,100
He won't last very long,
almost all the bones

361
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:40,090
in his torso are broken.

362
00:19:40,090 --> 00:19:42,130
Shishio, wait.

363
00:19:42,130 --> 00:19:46,040
Not yet.

364
00:19:46,040 --> 00:19:48,170
What?

365
00:19:48,170 --> 00:19:51,140
(grunting)

366
00:19:54,070 --> 00:19:57,210
Kori, I'm sorry that I
couldn't protect Kenshin.

367
00:20:02,180 --> 00:20:05,050
But this I swear.

368
00:20:07,050 --> 00:20:08,180
I won't give up.

369
00:20:08,180 --> 00:20:12,060
I'll fight this battle to
the end, to my last breath.

370
00:20:12,060 --> 00:20:34,090
♪

371
00:20:34,090 --> 00:20:37,120
(shouting)

372
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:41,250
♪

373
00:20:41,250 --> 00:20:43,180
I can't believe it!

374
00:20:43,180 --> 00:20:44,270
♪

375
00:20:44,270 --> 00:20:46,040
Ha!

376
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:48,000
That's the best
you've got, Sano?

377
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,180
Sorry, but it's just
not good enough.

378
00:20:50,180 --> 00:20:52,210
♪

379
00:20:52,210 --> 00:20:55,190
You should've left when
you had the opportunity.

380
00:20:55,190 --> 00:21:09,000
♪

381
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:12,180
(laughing)

382
00:21:12,180 --> 00:21:36,140
♪

383
00:21:36,140 --> 00:21:37,200
He's unstoppable.

384
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:38,280
No, he's more than that.

385
00:21:38,280 --> 00:21:40,290
Mr. Shishio is invulnerable.

386
00:21:40,290 --> 00:21:42,140
No one is as powerful.

387
00:21:42,140 --> 00:21:44,130
No one has his
indomitable will.

388
00:21:44,130 --> 00:21:48,040
He's the only one who can lead
Japan to the glory it deserves.

389
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:50,140
Finish him off now, Shishio.

390
00:21:50,140 --> 00:21:51,280
What are you waiting for?

391
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:54,220
He's helpless, kill
him, kill him now!

392
00:21:54,220 --> 00:21:56,120
Silence, Yumi!

393
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:59,290
I've won a great victory
today, and I wish to savor it.

394
00:21:59,290 --> 00:22:02,290
You must learn to
have patience, my dear.

395
00:22:02,290 --> 00:22:04,260
(laughing)

396
00:22:04,260 --> 00:22:06,010
You're wrong.

397
00:22:06,010 --> 00:22:07,180
(gasping)

398
00:22:07,180 --> 00:22:08,280
The day isn't over.

399
00:22:08,280 --> 00:22:11,170
You haven't won yet.

400
00:22:11,170 --> 00:22:19,040
♪

401
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:22,040
Aoshi, you must leave at once.

402
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:25,070
She's right,
you shouldn't have come, Aoshi.

403
00:22:25,070 --> 00:22:27,260
Your friends won't be
able to lend a hand,

404
00:22:27,260 --> 00:22:30,060
but you'll be joining
them shortly.

405
00:22:30,060 --> 00:22:33,060
(laughing)

406
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:45,130
♪

407
00:22:48,020 --> 00:23:11,210
♪

408
00:23:11,210 --> 00:23:15,030
(singing in foreign language)

409
00:23:15,030 --> 00:25:06,270
♪

